<BaseLayout title="PhilHealth & the cost of dialysis" description="An honest, plain-language explanation of PhilHealth's hemodialysis coverage — the per-session rate, sessions per year, No Balance Billing, and what to expect.">
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:720px">
      <a href="/kidney-health" style="font-weight:700;text-decoration:none">← Kidney Health Hub</a>
      <h1 style="margin-top:14px">PhilHealth &amp; the cost of dialysis</h1>
      <p class="lead">The question everyone's afraid to ask — answered as plainly as we can.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="font-size:.9rem">Adapted with permission from
        <a href={src}>renalcarematters.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>Does PhilHealth cover dialysis?</h2>
      <p>Yes. PhilHealth provides a dedicated <strong>hemodialysis benefit</strong> for eligible members,
      paid per session up to a set number of sessions each year. Bring your Member Data Record (MDR) and
      we'll help you check what applies to you.</p>

      <h2>The numbers, in plain terms</h2>
      <p>Under the latest PhilHealth circular, the hemodialysis package is
      <strong>₱6,350 per session</strong>, covering <strong>156 sessions per year</strong> — that's three
      sessions a week, all year — for a total of about <strong>₱990,600 a year</strong> of coverage.</p>
      <p>That package is designed to cover the core of a session: the facility and machine, the dialyzer,
      solutions and dialysis kit, anticoagulation, anemia medicines (ESA and IV iron), the related labs,
      and professional fees.</p>

      <div class="notice"><strong>No Balance Billing:</strong> at PhilHealth-accredited centers, there is
      <strong>no co-pay</strong> for the services included in the package for qualified members.</div>

      <h2>Beyond hemodialysis</h2>
      <p>PhilHealth also has separate “Z” benefit packages for <strong>peritoneal dialysis</strong> and
      <strong>kidney transplantation</strong>, which were substantially increased in 2025 — worth asking
      about if either may be right for you.</p>

      <h2>HMO &amp; other payment options</h2>
      <p>Beyond PhilHealth, we are <strong>HMO-accredited</strong> and accept <strong>various forms of
      payment</strong>. Bring your HMO card, and our team will help you check your coverage and choose the
      option that works best for you.</p>

      <h2>What will I actually pay?</h2>
      <p>It depends on your membership status, your remaining covered sessions, your HMO benefits, and any
      services outside the package. We'll sit with you and go through the real numbers for your situation —
      clearly, before your treatment, with no surprises.</p>

      <div class="notice" style="border-left-color:var(--life)">
        <strong>Please confirm current rates.</strong> PhilHealth benefits change through official
        circulars. Confirm the current figures with us or at <em>philhealth.gov.ph</em> before relying on
        them.
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top:20px"><a href="/new-patients#request" class="btn btn--primary">Ask us about your coverage</a></p>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top:22px;font-size:.9rem">
        Adapted with permission from <a href={src}>renalcarematters.com</a>. Reviewed for accuracy; rates
        reflect the latest PhilHealth circulars at the time of writing. We never overstate coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
